  "body": "<p>Hello everyone, it’s Zinia (aka <a href=\"http://abstractinspiration.com\">Abstract Inspiration</a>) and today I’d like to share with you a very easy and fun layout design you can create using only a few items.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/fc0446b9c67864de.jpg?v=1782796800\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>The inspiration came from the big floral paper that comes in the On a Whim collection. I really wanted to fussy cut some pieces and create a flowerpot of some sort. So after I cut a bunch of the flowers, I went to my paper stash to find a nice pattern for my base.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>I found this beautiful red striped paper but once I cut out a strip I fell in love with the way it looked spreading from one edge of the paper to the other. So instead of cutting it into a pot, I left it as is and starting building my flower cluster across the whole page.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/9d4eacd4c7c6ae04.jpg?v=1782796803\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Luckily, the flowers were big enough so I didn’t have a problem covering a big area with them. To make my cluster more interesting, I grabbed the On a Whim and Oh Happy Life sticker sheets and pulled more floral images and leaves. I used the floral stickers to fill the gaps between the bigger flowers and also balance the colors through the layout.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/b192790597564f49.jpg?v=1782796806\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>I didn’t want my title to be distracting so I picked some white foam words from the Oh Happy Life thicker pack and placed them vertically on the red striped paper. The red color was bright enough to create a nice contrast and still let the title pop a bit.</p><p>As for my photo, I used a black and white picture to help it stand out since everything else on this page was so bright and vibrant.</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/33302b353c60d024.jpg?v=1782796809\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>This design is really so easy and fun to make and as I said earlier you only need very minimal supplies. You can try different color combinations and patterns as well as mixing different types of flowers.</p><p>I really hope you enjoyed it and you will give it a go.</p><p>Zinia <br/><br/><a href=\"http://abstractinspiration.com/\">Abstract Inspiration Blog</a> | <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/abstractinspiration/\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"https://twitter.com/AbstractInsp\">Twitter</a> | <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/AbstractInspirationPage\">Facebook</a></p><p>Products used in this layout:<br/><br/><strong>378718 </strong>On a Whim 12x12 Pattern Paper - Full Bloom<strong> | 378734 </strong>On a Whim 12x12 Pattern Paper - Sprinkle<strong> | 378749 </strong>On a Whim ACCENT &amp; PHRASE STICKERS | <strong>376234</strong> Oh Happy Life ACCENT AND PHRASE STICKERS | <strong>376223</strong> Oh Happy Life THICKERS Wild | <strong>376231</strong> Oh Happy Life ROTARY STAMP</p><p><em>Thanks so much for sharing this lovely layout, Zinia! Shop ON A WHIM now! Check your local retailer and online at </em><a href=\"http://bit.ly/onawhim\"><em>Simon Says Stamp</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"http://bit.ly/amytangerineonawhim\"><em>Scrapbook.com</em></a></p><p><em>Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links. I receive a small percentage of sales at no cost to you. My creative partners and I really appreciate your continued support and every little bit helps me to bring you consistent content!</em></p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
